WEBVTT

00:01.634 --> 00:04.371
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.437 --> 00:11.378
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.445 --> 00:14.681
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.748 --> 00:16.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.483 --> 00:18.752
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.818 --> 00:24.424
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.491 --> 00:26.326
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.393 --> 00:29.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:31.631 --> 00:33.032
<i>[festive music]</i>

00:33.099 --> 00:35.068
<i>- 'Twas the night</i>
<i>before Halloween,</i>

00:35.135 --> 00:37.570
<i>and all through the town,</i>

00:37.637 --> 00:39.706
{\an8}<i>a spirit was lurking</i>

00:39.773 --> 00:41.875
{\an8}<i>and creeping around.</i>

00:41.941 --> 00:43.743
<i>They call him the Blargus.</i>

00:43.810 --> 00:45.879
<i>He comes out each year</i>

00:45.945 --> 00:47.614
<i>to scare up excitement</i>

00:47.680 --> 00:50.116
<i>and Halloween cheer.</i>

00:50.183 --> 00:52.585
<i>He watched children</i>
<i>make costumes</i>

00:52.652 --> 00:54.287
<i>because soon enough</i>

00:54.354 --> 00:56.189
<i>it'd be time to bug neighbors</i>

00:56.256 --> 00:58.958
<i>to give them free stuff.</i>

00:59.025 --> 01:01.594
<i>All except one child,</i>

01:01.661 --> 01:03.797
<i>a studly bear cub</i>

01:03.863 --> 01:06.166
<i>who at this very moment</i>

01:06.232 --> 01:09.235
<i>was rolling to the club.</i>

01:09.302 --> 01:10.904
[growling]

01:10.970 --> 01:13.907
{\an8}<i>[festive techno music]</i>

01:13.973 --> 01:21.114
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:28.154 --> 01:29.689
{\an1}- Hey, there, boo.
Get it?

01:29.756 --> 01:32.559
{\an1}Ghosts? Halloween?
Ey, cutie!

01:32.625 --> 01:34.360
Your dance moves are bewitching.

01:34.427 --> 01:36.830
{\an3}I want to make you
my baby ghoul.

01:36.896 --> 01:38.665
Man, I am good at flirting.

01:38.731 --> 01:40.667
- Hey, there.

01:40.733 --> 01:42.502
You look thirsty.

01:42.569 --> 01:44.904
Let me buy you a pop.

01:44.971 --> 01:47.040
- Whoa, thanks, pretty lady.

01:47.106 --> 01:49.042
- [gasps] You think I'm pretty?

01:49.108 --> 01:51.478
[giddy laughter]

01:51.544 --> 01:54.581
{\an1}- So, anyways,
what's your name, sugar?

01:54.647 --> 01:55.915
You look sweet as candy.

01:55.982 --> 01:58.051
- My name is literally Candy.

01:58.117 --> 02:00.286
- That's hot.

02:00.353 --> 02:01.888
{\an3}- Thanks.

02:01.955 --> 02:04.157
- Wait, do you got a lazy eye,

02:04.224 --> 02:05.792
or are you flirting with me?

02:05.859 --> 02:06.860
{\an3}- Yeah.

02:06.926 --> 02:08.127
- [gasping]

02:08.193 --> 02:10.128
- We should, like,
hang out tomorrow.

02:10.196 --> 02:12.265
- That's a great idea!
Tomorrow is Halloween.

02:12.332 --> 02:13.967
We can go trick-or-treating.

02:14.033 --> 02:15.969
{\an3}- You're going
trick-or-treating?

02:16.035 --> 02:17.937
- Uh, you're not?

02:18.004 --> 02:19.639
- Um, yeah, right.

02:19.706 --> 02:21.140
I'm not a baby.

02:21.207 --> 02:23.076
{\an3}I'll be here at the club
tomorrow night

02:23.142 --> 02:26.079
doing this...

02:26.145 --> 02:28.381
- Oh, yeah. Me too.
I was just playing.

02:28.448 --> 02:31.284
{\an1}Trick-or-treating is, like,
way lame.

02:31.351 --> 02:33.152
- Yeah, tell me about it.

02:33.219 --> 02:36.589
- I mean, who cares about
free candy anyway, right?

02:36.656 --> 02:37.590
[forced laugh]

02:37.657 --> 02:39.893
- [laughing]

02:39.959 --> 02:43.096
[obnoxious laughter]

02:52.071 --> 02:54.774
Cool. So I'll see you tomorrow.

02:54.841 --> 02:56.376
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:56.442 --> 02:59.746
<i>[festive music]</i>

02:59.812 --> 03:01.614
- Happy Halloween, everyone.

03:01.681 --> 03:03.149
- Nice costume, Piri Piri.

03:03.216 --> 03:04.884
{\an1}You're the amalgamation
of hopes

03:04.951 --> 03:06.619
{\an1}and dreams
of every child, right?

03:06.686 --> 03:07.887
{\an3}- Exactly!

03:07.954 --> 03:09.656
{\an3}Oh, and you're
a washing machine.

03:09.722 --> 03:11.758
- What? No.
I'm a robot.

03:11.824 --> 03:15.862
{\an3}- Why do you have a dirty
sock on your head then?

03:15.929 --> 03:17.597
- I don't know.

03:17.664 --> 03:19.098
- [groans] I'm hungry.

03:19.165 --> 03:20.733
Isn't Harvey ready yet?

03:20.800 --> 03:22.635
- [imitating siren]

03:22.702 --> 03:25.405
Happy Halloween from
your local fire department.

03:25.471 --> 03:28.041
You know, it's tough out there
for a firefighter

03:28.107 --> 03:30.476
who can only fight fires
by moonlight

03:30.543 --> 03:33.780
because I'm also
a bloodsucking vampire!

03:33.846 --> 03:35.081
[evil laugh]

03:35.148 --> 03:38.952
And this is my evil,
yet adorable, minion.

03:39.018 --> 03:40.753
We all ready to go, gang?

03:40.820 --> 03:43.523
Hey, wait a second.

03:43.590 --> 03:45.925
Someone is missing.

03:45.992 --> 03:48.261
Oh, where's Technobear?

03:48.328 --> 03:50.997
{\an3}- Oy, we can't trick-or-treat
without TB.

03:51.064 --> 03:52.832
He makes Halloween a party.

03:52.899 --> 03:54.367
We--we can't go without him.

03:54.434 --> 03:57.070
{\an1}- All right, Rooter.
Calm down already.

03:57.136 --> 03:58.771
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

03:58.838 --> 04:01.774
- [imitating siren]

04:02.942 --> 04:04.911
- Hey! Whoa!

04:04.978 --> 04:07.080
Where's the fire, bro?

04:07.146 --> 04:08.314
- Hi, Mr. Snapper.

04:08.381 --> 04:09.782
What are you dressed as?

04:09.849 --> 04:13.052
{\an3}- Me? Oh.
I'm a tall glass of water.

04:13.119 --> 04:16.255
{\an3}- [giggles]
And I'm thirsty.

04:16.322 --> 04:18.224
- I feel uncomfortable.

04:18.291 --> 04:19.858
{\an1}- We're here
to pick up Technobear.

04:19.926 --> 04:21.361
- Hey, Ma, can you iron

04:21.427 --> 04:23.830
{\an3}my lucky briefs
for me real quick?

04:23.896 --> 04:26.466
Oh, uh, hey, guys.

04:26.532 --> 04:28.601
{\an1}- Technobear,
where's your costume?

04:28.668 --> 04:31.037
{\an3}- Costume?
Nah, come on, man.

04:31.104 --> 04:32.839
I ain't doing that anymore.

04:32.905 --> 04:34.173
[all gasping]

04:34.240 --> 04:36.009
{\an3}- But you love
trick-or-treating.

04:36.075 --> 04:38.911
{\an3}- Uh, yeah, I mean, I loved it
when I was itty-bitty,

04:38.978 --> 04:40.446
but I'm a big boy now.

04:40.513 --> 04:42.782
{\an1}- But who's gonna bring
the glow sticks?

04:42.849 --> 04:44.917
- Yeah, and the boom box.

04:44.984 --> 04:47.020
- Who's gonna bring the party?

04:47.086 --> 04:48.488
- I...well...

04:48.554 --> 04:51.891
{\an1}- Technobear, who's gonna
bring the party?

04:51.958 --> 04:53.059
- Um, well...

04:53.126 --> 04:55.294
<i>- Don't be a baby.</i>

04:55.361 --> 04:58.398
<i>Seriously, don't.</i>

04:58.464 --> 05:00.233
- No.
I've made up my mind.

05:00.299 --> 05:02.702
Y'all need to respect
my manly decisions.

05:02.769 --> 05:04.270
all: Aww.

05:04.337 --> 05:06.606
- Well, I want you to have this.

05:06.673 --> 05:08.975
{\an1}In case they don't have
candy at the club.

05:09.042 --> 05:10.510
- Oh, thanks, man.

05:10.576 --> 05:13.212
{\an3}But I'm pretty sure they got
candy at the club.

05:13.279 --> 05:16.382
<i>- My name's literally Candy.</i>

05:16.449 --> 05:19.452
- Bye, Mr. and Mrs. Snapper.

05:19.519 --> 05:24.023
{\an1}- I don't get it.
He used to love Halloween.

05:24.090 --> 05:27.226
- [growling]

05:29.195 --> 05:30.997
- Goin' to the club!

05:31.064 --> 05:33.099
Aw, yeah.
Gonna dance it up.

05:33.166 --> 05:35.034
Do a little bit of this.
Unh!

05:35.101 --> 05:36.936
Oh, yeah!

05:37.003 --> 05:40.139
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

05:41.941 --> 05:43.209
<i>[rustling]</i>

05:43.276 --> 05:45.011
What was that?

05:45.078 --> 05:46.012
<i>[owl hooting]</i>

05:46.079 --> 05:48.781
Hmm, just trees.

05:48.848 --> 05:51.818
- [evil laughter]

05:51.884 --> 05:54.153
<i>[wind howling]</i>

05:54.220 --> 05:55.822
- Weird.

05:55.888 --> 05:58.057
- Boo!
- [screaming]

05:58.124 --> 06:01.127
{\an3}Ouch!
Dang it! Stubbed my toe!

06:01.194 --> 06:03.496
{\an3}Hey, bro.
What are you supposed to be?

06:03.563 --> 06:06.199
{\an3}Oh, you're the Grimbus.
That's cute.

06:06.265 --> 06:07.433
- I'm the Blargus!

06:07.500 --> 06:10.470
And I'm terrifying!

06:10.536 --> 06:12.205
- That's a good costume.

06:12.271 --> 06:14.107
{\an3}Who's in there?
Is that you, Harvey?

06:14.173 --> 06:16.142
- Ah! Stop that!

06:16.209 --> 06:18.411
<i>Technobear,</i>

06:18.478 --> 06:20.179
<i>you have forgotten</i>

06:20.246 --> 06:22.782
<i>the true meaning of Halloween,</i>

06:22.849 --> 06:25.251
<i>so tonight,</i>
<i>you'll be visited</i>

06:25.318 --> 06:27.987
<i>by three Halloween spirits!</i>

06:28.054 --> 06:30.456
{\an3}- Ooh.

06:30.523 --> 06:34.327
{\an1}- To remind you what Halloween
is really about.

06:34.393 --> 06:36.295
- What?
- To remind you--

06:36.362 --> 06:37.530
- No, no. The other thing.

06:37.597 --> 06:41.434
- Uh, three Halloween ghosts.

06:44.837 --> 06:47.006
- What?
- Ah! Whatever!

06:47.073 --> 06:48.741
You'll see soon enough.

06:48.808 --> 06:50.910
Be ready, Technobear.

06:50.977 --> 06:53.913
<i>[evil laughter]</i>

06:53.980 --> 06:54.981
[bats squealing]

06:55.047 --> 06:56.182
- Yo, Drangus.

06:56.249 --> 06:58.251
Those were some dope
special effects.

06:58.317 --> 07:00.820
<i>[doorbell ringing]</i>

07:00.887 --> 07:02.121
all: Trick or treat!

07:02.188 --> 07:05.158
{\an1}- Oh, my.
Look at you little cuties.

07:05.224 --> 07:07.760
{\an1}Now, where's the little
dancing bear?

07:07.827 --> 07:09.061
I was hoping to see him

07:09.128 --> 07:11.664
one more time before I pass.

07:11.731 --> 07:14.000
- Oh.
He's not here, actually.

07:14.066 --> 07:16.002
But we can dance for you.

07:16.068 --> 07:18.704
Foo?

07:21.574 --> 07:23.409
<i>[door slamming]</i>
- Dental floss?

07:23.476 --> 07:25.011
Are you kidding me, lady?

07:25.077 --> 07:26.445
You guys having any luck?

07:26.512 --> 07:28.514
- I got some cold oatmeal.

07:28.581 --> 07:30.016
- I got this apple,

07:30.082 --> 07:31.851
but it's got a tooth in it.

07:31.918 --> 07:33.719
- I got a high-five.

07:33.786 --> 07:34.520
{\an1}From Piri.

07:34.587 --> 07:36.656
- And I got plenty more!

07:36.722 --> 07:38.124
- I got spit on!

07:38.191 --> 07:39.559
- If Technobear were here,

07:39.625 --> 07:41.661
we'd be swimming
in candy by now.

07:41.727 --> 07:44.730
{\an1}- He always made this night
really fun.

07:44.797 --> 07:47.099
all: [sighing]

07:47.166 --> 07:50.102
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

07:50.169 --> 07:51.170
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:51.237 --> 07:52.438
- Man, it's a longer walk

07:52.505 --> 07:54.240
to the club than I remembered.

07:54.307 --> 07:55.775
- [evil laughter]

07:55.842 --> 07:57.176
{\an1}- Huh?

07:57.243 --> 07:59.312
Hmm.

07:59.378 --> 08:01.147
- Hello!
- Ah!

08:01.214 --> 08:02.815
What the dump?
Who are you?

08:02.882 --> 08:06.219
- I'm the Ghost
of Halloween Past!

08:06.285 --> 08:07.687
- [gasps]

08:07.753 --> 08:09.522
Yo, Foo, your head's on fire.

08:09.589 --> 08:12.892
You're really stepping up
on your costume game, bro.

08:12.959 --> 08:15.661
Anyway, see you.
- Wait! You can't leave yet.

08:15.728 --> 08:17.530
We need to revisit your past.

08:17.597 --> 08:19.265
- Say what?
- Uh...

08:19.332 --> 08:21.367
{\an3}I mean...

08:21.434 --> 08:23.202
{\an3}Let me give you
a ride to the club.

08:23.269 --> 08:24.904
On my time bike.

08:24.971 --> 08:26.272
- Oh. Thanks, bro.

08:26.339 --> 08:27.740
- No problem.

08:27.807 --> 08:30.776
{\an3}- Uh, Foo, I don't think
this is the right way.

08:30.843 --> 08:31.777
- Oopsies.

08:31.844 --> 08:33.913
[clock dinging]

08:35.214 --> 08:37.817
{\an3}- This don't look like
the club, man.

08:37.884 --> 08:40.253
- Look.

08:40.318 --> 08:42.255
- Yo, wait a minute.

08:42.321 --> 08:43.956
<i>Is that little baby Harvey?</i>

08:44.023 --> 08:45.191
<i>And little baby Dade?</i>

08:45.258 --> 08:47.393
- Hey, Harvey,
Harvey, Harvey,

08:47.460 --> 08:48.861
Harvey, Harvey, Harvey.

08:48.928 --> 08:50.029
<i>- And baby Claire,</i>

08:50.096 --> 08:51.564
<i>and baby Kratz?</i>

08:51.631 --> 08:53.900
<i>[gasps] And there's</i>
<i>little baby me.</i>

08:53.966 --> 08:57.103
Aww.
- You were a beautiful baby.

08:57.169 --> 08:59.372
{\an7}- Now it's time
to grow up, babies!

08:59.438 --> 09:01.507
{\an8}- My passie! You wrecked it!

09:01.574 --> 09:03.542
{\an7}- We going
trick-or-treating, y'all!

09:03.609 --> 09:05.945
{\an3}- But we're too young
to trick-or-treat.

09:06.012 --> 09:07.980
- We're only three!

09:08.047 --> 09:09.348
- It sound scary.

09:09.415 --> 09:11.350
{\an1}- Yeah, but it's the good
kind of scary.

09:11.417 --> 09:12.919
The kind that gets you candy.

09:12.985 --> 09:14.053
{\an3}- Ooh!

09:14.120 --> 09:15.955
{\an1}- And you get to wear
anything you want.

09:16.022 --> 09:17.123
{\an3}- Really?

09:17.189 --> 09:19.258
{\an3}- Harvey, you can practice
socializing.

09:19.325 --> 09:20.626
- Ooh!

09:20.693 --> 09:22.962
- Dade, Harvey's going.

09:23.029 --> 09:24.230
{\an1}- Ooh!

09:24.297 --> 09:25.731
- Come on, guys!
Let's do this!

09:25.798 --> 09:28.968
all: Yeah!
- I'm excited.

09:29.035 --> 09:31.103
- Aw, those were good times.

09:31.170 --> 09:33.172
- Good times with good babies.

09:33.239 --> 09:35.274
{\an1}And of all the babies,
you were always

09:35.341 --> 09:37.009
the most grown-up baby.

09:37.076 --> 09:38.878
Weren't you, Mr. Baby?

09:38.945 --> 09:40.346
- Huh?
- Let's go, baby!

09:40.413 --> 09:41.514
{\an3}- Whoa!

09:41.580 --> 09:42.515
<i>[doorbell ringing]</i>
Wha?

09:42.581 --> 09:43.516
<i>[door opening]</i>

09:43.582 --> 09:45.318
all: Trick or treat!

09:45.384 --> 09:46.752
{\an3}- Oh, my.

09:46.819 --> 09:49.522
{\an3}How nice to see
some fresh little faces

09:49.588 --> 09:51.457
before I pass.

09:51.524 --> 09:53.926
- I'm a bunny,
but also a goblin.

09:53.993 --> 09:56.395
- I'm a disco ball.

09:56.462 --> 09:58.931
<i>[techno music playing]</i>
[grunting]

09:58.998 --> 10:00.599
- Oh. Oh. Ooh!

10:00.666 --> 10:02.301
Dance! Dance! Dance!

10:02.368 --> 10:04.870
Oh, wonderful!

10:04.937 --> 10:06.872
Just wonderful!

10:06.939 --> 10:09.842
all: Yay!

10:09.909 --> 10:11.310
{\an3}- So?

10:11.377 --> 10:13.312
How do you feel?

10:13.379 --> 10:15.147
- I feel like...

10:15.214 --> 10:16.415
{\an1}like...

10:16.482 --> 10:18.284
like I ain't no baby no more!

10:18.351 --> 10:20.119
{\an1}Now I know for sure
I'm a big boy,

10:20.186 --> 10:21.587
and I got to do
big boy things

10:21.654 --> 10:22.989
at the big boy club.

10:23.055 --> 10:25.992
{\an1}Thanks for the trip
down memory lane, Foo.

10:26.058 --> 10:27.426
Peace!
- Okay!

10:27.493 --> 10:28.661
Bye, Technobear.

10:28.728 --> 10:31.230
Have fun with the other ghosts.

10:31.297 --> 10:34.166
That went well.
- [groaning]

10:34.233 --> 10:35.167
<i>[scary music]</i>

10:35.234 --> 10:36.235
<i>[wolf howling]</i>

10:36.302 --> 10:37.470
- Huh, I don't remember

10:37.536 --> 10:38.504
there being a pumpkin patch

10:38.571 --> 10:39.739
on the way to the club.

10:39.805 --> 10:41.340
Maybe I should bring a pumpkin

10:41.407 --> 10:43.009
for my pumpkin.
[chuckles]

10:43.075 --> 10:45.711
Actually, this kind of
looks like Candy.

10:45.778 --> 10:48.280
{\an3}Kind of want to kiss it.
Mm...

10:48.347 --> 10:49.849
- You sure about that?

10:49.915 --> 10:50.883
{\an3}- Whoa!

10:50.950 --> 10:52.184
Dude! Harvey!

10:52.251 --> 10:54.920
What are you supposed to be?

10:54.987 --> 10:55.921
- Ta-da!

10:55.988 --> 10:57.156
{\an3}- Okay, so,

10:57.223 --> 10:58.891
{\an3}you're some kind of
pumpkin ghost?

10:58.958 --> 11:02.094
{\an1}- Open this gift,
and you'll find out.

11:02.161 --> 11:03.162
- It's empty.

11:03.229 --> 11:04.563
- That's because the gift

11:04.630 --> 11:06.165
is the present.

11:06.232 --> 11:07.166
{\an3}- What?

11:07.233 --> 11:08.901
- And the present is a gift.

11:08.968 --> 11:11.504
- This present is very empty.

11:11.570 --> 11:14.006
- So, have you guessed it?

11:14.073 --> 11:15.207
- Literally nothing.

11:15.274 --> 11:17.209
- Have you guessed it?

11:17.276 --> 11:18.611
- I'm so confused.

11:18.677 --> 11:20.946
{\an1}- I'm the Ghost
of Halloween Present!

11:21.013 --> 11:22.481
{\an3}- Oh! Okay.

11:22.548 --> 11:23.682
I get it now.

11:23.749 --> 11:25.151
{\an1}- Great.
Now come with me.

11:25.217 --> 11:27.253
{\an3}- Whoa!

11:27.319 --> 11:29.455
Cool, so you can
fly now, Harvey?

11:29.522 --> 11:31.057
{\an1}You got to tell me
your workout routine.

11:31.123 --> 11:34.026
{\an3}- I am only here
to show you your present.

11:34.093 --> 11:34.994
{\an3}Behold!

11:35.061 --> 11:36.529
- Ey, there's all my buddies!

11:36.595 --> 11:38.297
Ey, wait a second.

11:38.364 --> 11:41.167
{\an1}That's Harvey.
But...

11:41.233 --> 11:42.501
You're right here.

11:42.568 --> 11:44.437
{\an1}Unless...

11:44.503 --> 11:47.139
You really are a ghost.

11:47.206 --> 11:48.908
- Course I am, silly.

11:48.974 --> 11:51.110
[screams]
- Oh, snap!

11:52.545 --> 11:53.546
- Oh, snap!

11:53.612 --> 11:54.580
{\an1}Wait, wait, wait,
wait a second.

11:54.647 --> 11:55.981
Rewind. Back up.

11:56.048 --> 11:59.351
{\an1}So you're Harvey,
and that's normal Harvey.

11:59.418 --> 12:00.820
- Yep.
- Hmm...

12:00.886 --> 12:04.223
Ghost Harvey, normal Harvey.
Ghost Harvey, normal Harvey.

12:04.290 --> 12:06.358
Ghost Harvey, normal Harvey,
ghost Harvey, normal Harvey,

12:06.425 --> 12:07.893
ghost Harvey, normal Harvey--
- Stop that.

12:07.960 --> 12:09.695
- Ah!
- Like I said,

12:09.762 --> 12:11.730
{\an3}I'm the Ghost of
Halloween Present.

12:11.797 --> 12:15.301
I want to show you something.

12:15.367 --> 12:17.470
- Now, this is what
I'm talking about.

12:17.536 --> 12:20.706
Look at this place.
It's like Halloween central.

12:20.773 --> 12:23.409
{\an3}We're gonna get
tons of candy here.

12:23.476 --> 12:25.111
- Well, okay.

12:25.177 --> 12:27.780
I just really hope
this sign's a typo.

12:27.847 --> 12:29.782
{\an3}- No, no!
What are they doing?

12:29.849 --> 12:32.251
That house spent all their
money on the decorations.

12:32.318 --> 12:34.353
It's always that
moderately-decorated house

12:34.420 --> 12:37.423
{\an3}across the street that's
got the best candy.

12:37.490 --> 12:39.225
- Ah, slow year.

12:39.291 --> 12:42.495
Oh, well.

12:42.561 --> 12:44.363
all: [whimpering]

12:44.430 --> 12:46.732
- Oh, I'm deathly uncomfortable.

12:46.799 --> 12:48.300
<i>- Foo is so brave.</i>

12:48.367 --> 12:50.402
<i>I wonder what</i>
<i>he's thinking about.</i>

12:50.469 --> 12:53.572
<i>- I've peed in this costume</i>
<i>three times.</i>

12:53.639 --> 12:55.574
- Listen: If you want
the good stuff,

12:55.641 --> 12:57.042
you got to earn it--
ooh!

12:57.109 --> 12:58.811
- [screaming]
all: [gasping]

12:58.878 --> 13:00.546
- [laughing]
all: [screaming]

13:00.613 --> 13:03.749
[screaming]

13:06.118 --> 13:08.087
It's just a stupid machine.

13:08.154 --> 13:11.023
- [laughing]
- He's laughing at me.

13:11.090 --> 13:12.892
- Come on, Harvey,
just give it a punch

13:12.958 --> 13:13.926
in the old kisser.

13:13.993 --> 13:16.095
- [laughing]
- [grunts]

13:16.162 --> 13:17.663
- [laughing]

13:17.730 --> 13:19.365
- He's still going!

13:19.431 --> 13:21.333
all: Ah!

13:21.400 --> 13:22.568
- [whimpering]

13:22.635 --> 13:25.504
- Boo!
- Ah!

13:25.571 --> 13:28.707
- [grunting]

13:29.842 --> 13:31.010
- What are they doing?

13:31.076 --> 13:34.513
{\an1}Don't they know
whose house this is?

13:34.580 --> 13:36.248
- What is going on here?

13:36.315 --> 13:38.417
- [grunting] Oh.

13:38.484 --> 13:40.252
- My beautiful decorations!

13:40.319 --> 13:41.420
{\an3}[gasps]

13:41.487 --> 13:43.689
{\an3}What did you do to
Frankenstein...

13:43.756 --> 13:44.957
{\an3}'s monster!

13:45.024 --> 13:47.459
- Uh...trick or treat?

13:47.526 --> 13:49.628
- [growling]

13:49.695 --> 13:52.064
all: [screaming]

13:52.131 --> 13:53.499
{\an3}- Oh, man.

13:53.566 --> 13:55.834
{\an3}They're pretty terrible
at trick-or-treating.

13:55.901 --> 13:58.637
{\an3}Well, they'll score
at the next house, right?

13:58.704 --> 14:00.906
{\an1}- Without you there,
I don't know.

14:00.973 --> 14:02.841
- Oh.
- Oh.

14:02.908 --> 14:05.244
{\an1}Got to get my pumpkin pie
out of the oven.

14:05.311 --> 14:06.712
- Pumpkin pie?

14:06.779 --> 14:09.481
But your head is a--
- Pumpkin?

14:09.548 --> 14:12.184
I know.

14:12.251 --> 14:13.852
Happy Halloween!

14:13.919 --> 14:16.222
[evil laughter]

14:16.288 --> 14:19.158
- Ew, now that is
one sick dude.

14:19.225 --> 14:22.361
Ah!

14:22.428 --> 14:24.730
Ooh!

14:24.797 --> 14:26.665
Oh, man, it hurts to see

14:26.732 --> 14:28.834
my friends strike out like that.

14:28.901 --> 14:31.537
- Yes, so close.

14:31.604 --> 14:33.806
Go forth, and complete

14:33.872 --> 14:36.575
the return of the Technobear

14:36.642 --> 14:40.012
to the Eve of Hallow.

14:40.079 --> 14:42.915
- Huh?
- To finish the job!

14:43.949 --> 14:45.684
- Okay, third ghost.

14:45.751 --> 14:47.286
You're getting a little

14:47.353 --> 14:49.421
fashionably late here.

14:49.488 --> 14:53.092
Yo, what is that?

14:53.158 --> 14:55.194
{\an1}Yo!

14:55.261 --> 14:56.996
{\an1}Yo.

14:57.062 --> 14:58.197
Yo--
- Sup?

14:58.264 --> 14:59.231
{\an1}- Ah!

14:59.298 --> 15:00.232
{\an1}Oh, wait.

15:00.299 --> 15:01.267
You're ghost Fee.

15:01.333 --> 15:03.235
{\an7}I was kind of hoping
for ghost Miriam,

15:03.302 --> 15:06.138
{\an7}but I guess this one
makes more sense.

15:06.205 --> 15:08.507
{\an7}Oh--ah!

15:08.574 --> 15:10.709
{\an8}Why am I always falling?

15:10.776 --> 15:12.278
{\an8}Ah!

15:12.344 --> 15:13.345
{\an8}Ooh!

15:13.412 --> 15:15.481
{\an9}- Dude.

15:15.547 --> 15:18.083
{\an8}- Is this the future?

15:18.150 --> 15:19.318
[gasps]

15:19.385 --> 15:21.253
The future is...

15:21.320 --> 15:24.456
a club!

15:24.523 --> 15:26.492
Oh, yeah, baby!

15:26.558 --> 15:29.328
Technobear is in the hizz-ouse!

15:29.395 --> 15:30.729
{\an3}Huh?

15:30.796 --> 15:32.931
Where is everybody?

15:32.998 --> 15:35.868
Yo, yo, this place is, like,
super dead.

15:35.934 --> 15:38.637
[blowing]

15:38.704 --> 15:41.340
Yo, yo, yo, yo,
this place is, like,

15:41.407 --> 15:43.208
super-duper dead.

15:43.275 --> 15:44.910
What are you trying to tell me
by taking me

15:44.977 --> 15:48.180
to the deadest dead club
that ever dropped dead?

15:48.247 --> 15:50.516
Ah! Ooh!

15:50.582 --> 15:51.684
{\an8}[gasps]

15:51.750 --> 15:53.619
{\an8}This place is dead because

15:53.686 --> 15:55.354
{\an9}I'm dead!

15:55.421 --> 15:57.690
{\an8}No!
There's got to be a mistake!

15:57.756 --> 15:59.658
{\an8}I can't be dead.
I'm right here.

15:59.725 --> 16:01.493
{\an7}- Dude.

16:01.560 --> 16:04.563
{\an8}<i>[scary music]</i>

16:04.630 --> 16:07.566
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:07.633 --> 16:09.034
- Nah, bro. We dead.

16:09.101 --> 16:11.203
{\an3}- No, there's got to be
something I can do!

16:11.270 --> 16:13.972
{\an3}A lesson I could learn.
I don't want to die tonight!

16:14.039 --> 16:16.075
{\an1}- Nah, bro.
We don't die tonight.

16:16.141 --> 16:18.510
- We don't?
- Nah, not for a long time.

16:18.577 --> 16:20.079
- Oh, cool, so you want
to hit the club, then?

16:20.145 --> 16:21.914
- Bro, I thought
you'd never ask.

16:21.980 --> 16:23.449
both: Ey!

16:23.515 --> 16:25.351
- [groans]

16:25.417 --> 16:27.586
<i>[techno music]</i>

16:27.653 --> 16:29.188
- You want to boogie with us?

16:29.254 --> 16:30.989
<i>♪</i> ♪

16:31.056 --> 16:32.925
- No, no, no!

16:32.991 --> 16:35.027
Shut it down!

16:37.162 --> 16:39.164
{\an3}Fine!
Don't trick or treat!

16:39.231 --> 16:41.500
I don't care anymore!

16:41.567 --> 16:43.869
{\an3}[sighs]
You're just another kid

16:43.936 --> 16:46.672
who lost the Halloween spirit.

16:46.739 --> 16:48.941
{\an1}- So...I can
go to the club?

16:49.007 --> 16:50.476
{\an3}- Get out!

16:50.542 --> 16:52.111
- You know, dude,
I'm gonna send you

16:52.177 --> 16:55.781
{\an1}those three ghosts to talk
about your anger management.

16:55.848 --> 16:58.050
All right, bro.
Happy Halloween.

16:58.117 --> 16:59.852
- That's right,
you little con artists.

16:59.918 --> 17:01.086
Get out of here.

17:01.153 --> 17:02.588
You want candy,
you got to pay for it

17:02.654 --> 17:04.056
like everyone else.

17:04.123 --> 17:06.125
- Nothing in life is free.

17:06.191 --> 17:10.028
- This whole night
has been a big bust.

17:12.931 --> 17:15.166
- Maybe we are getting
too old for this.

17:15.233 --> 17:17.502
{\an3}- We're nothing without
Technobear.

17:17.569 --> 17:19.104
It was all in his charm.

17:19.171 --> 17:21.707
{\an1}- We didn't even
get any candy.

17:21.773 --> 17:23.575
- Speak for yourself.

17:23.642 --> 17:24.843
all: [gasping]

17:24.910 --> 17:27.112
- Fee, you bought
candy from Randl?

17:27.179 --> 17:29.515
- Yeah...I bought it...

17:29.581 --> 17:31.683
{\an8}Anyway, I wasn't
gonna let Halloween

17:31.750 --> 17:33.285
{\an8}be a total disaster.

17:33.352 --> 17:34.820
{\an8}all: [gasping]
- Oh, I love it.

17:34.887 --> 17:38.690
{\an7}It's my own child.
Oh, I love it so much.

17:38.757 --> 17:40.826
{\an3}- One for you,
and one for you.

17:40.893 --> 17:42.761
- I don't even want to eat it.

17:42.828 --> 17:44.496
I just want to stare at it.

17:44.563 --> 17:47.199
{\an3}- It's a Halloween miracle,
plain and simple.

17:47.266 --> 17:51.336
[thunder and lightning]

17:51.403 --> 17:54.339
[gasping]

17:56.508 --> 17:58.944
- No. No. No. No!

17:59.011 --> 18:01.079
{\an8}all: [sobbing]

18:01.146 --> 18:04.983
{\an7}- This is the worst
Halloween ever!

18:05.050 --> 18:07.886
{\an1}- Ey, I finally made it.
Club Mulch.

18:07.953 --> 18:10.889
All right. Let's do this.

18:10.956 --> 18:13.892
<i>[dance music]</i>

18:13.959 --> 18:18.330
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:18.397 --> 18:20.732
- Oh, no. Ah! Ah!
It's in my eyes!

18:20.799 --> 18:22.301
[screaming]

18:22.367 --> 18:25.938
- Yeah!
Now these are my people!

18:26.004 --> 18:27.372
Hot stuff!
- What's up?

18:27.439 --> 18:28.574
{\an3}- Hot cake!

18:28.640 --> 18:29.942
- Don't look at me
when I'm dancing.

18:30.008 --> 18:32.444
- Hot...Candy?

18:32.511 --> 18:34.746
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:34.813 --> 18:36.949
Sweet moves, Candy.

18:37.015 --> 18:38.350
- Oh, Technobear.

18:38.417 --> 18:39.618
{\an3}I thought you were out
trick-or-treating

18:39.685 --> 18:42.087
{\an3}with your weird little
baby friends.

18:42.154 --> 18:43.989
So glad you ditched them.

18:44.056 --> 18:46.125
- Yeah, I don't
miss my friends.

18:46.191 --> 18:47.493
Or trick-or-treating.

18:47.559 --> 18:49.695
{\an3}- Why go trick-or-treating
when you got

18:49.761 --> 18:52.364
Candy right here.

18:52.431 --> 18:54.867
- Yeah. Great.

18:54.933 --> 18:56.401
- What's wrong?
- Nothing!

18:56.468 --> 18:58.804
{\an1}We're dancing.
This is fun.

18:58.871 --> 19:00.706
No guilt whatsoever.

19:00.772 --> 19:02.641
{\an8}<i>[growling]</i>

19:02.708 --> 19:04.276
{\an8}Yo, I'm getting hungry.

19:04.343 --> 19:07.012
{\an7}You wouldn't happen to have any
real candy on you, would you?

19:07.079 --> 19:09.047
{\an3}- [laughing]
What?

19:09.114 --> 19:11.183
- Uh...never mind.

19:11.250 --> 19:13.519
Hey, bro, do you or
your friends have candy?

19:13.585 --> 19:16.121
{\an1}- Sorry, no candy,
and these are not my friends.

19:16.188 --> 19:17.789
I abandoned my friends years ago

19:17.856 --> 19:21.894
{\an1}'cause all they wanted to do
was trick-or-treat.

19:21.960 --> 19:23.762
I miss my friends.

19:23.829 --> 19:25.030
{\an1}And candy.

19:25.097 --> 19:26.899
- I too have turned my back

19:26.965 --> 19:29.268
{\an1}on both friends
and trick-or-treating.

19:29.334 --> 19:30.502
- One day you're out
trick-or-treating

19:30.569 --> 19:32.304
with your best friends,
the next

19:32.371 --> 19:34.907
you're clubbing, and then
the next, you're dead.

19:34.973 --> 19:37.609
[sobbing]

19:37.676 --> 19:41.547
{\an3}- Ew, stop talking
about trick-or-treating.

19:41.613 --> 19:44.016
- Did someone say
trick-or-treating?

19:44.082 --> 19:46.018
{\an1}- Yeah, I miss trick-or-treating
with friends.

19:46.084 --> 19:47.586
- There's no candy
here at the club!

19:47.653 --> 19:49.421
- Why did I choose
to go clubbing

19:49.488 --> 19:51.290
without friends on Halloween?

19:51.356 --> 19:53.191
- Just wish I could go
back to that time.

19:53.258 --> 19:54.826
I want to go back!

19:54.893 --> 19:56.662
all: [sobbing]

19:56.728 --> 19:58.664
{\an3}- Ugh!
You're all just a bunch

19:58.730 --> 20:02.134
of little crying babies!

20:02.200 --> 20:04.570
I'm just gonna dance
by myself then.

20:04.636 --> 20:08.006
<i>[techno music]</i>

20:08.073 --> 20:10.042
- Now I'm hungry and sad.

20:10.108 --> 20:11.043
<i>[dinging]</i>

20:11.109 --> 20:13.946
[gasps]
Huh?

20:14.012 --> 20:17.716
- In case they don't have
candy at the club.

20:21.787 --> 20:24.423
- Hmm...

20:24.489 --> 20:27.292
{\an1}- Guys, maybe we should look
on the bright side.

20:27.359 --> 20:30.295
{\an1}I mean, I did find this
piece of broccoli.

20:30.362 --> 20:32.564
I know it's not sweet, but--
- No.

20:32.631 --> 20:35.167
{\an3}Wrong. No.

20:35.233 --> 20:37.603
{\an1}- I was supposed to be
a magical girl,

20:37.669 --> 20:40.205
{\an1}but there's nothing magical
about tonight.

20:40.272 --> 20:41.940
{\an3}- Candy! Where's the candy?
Do you have it?

20:42.007 --> 20:43.609
- [screaming]

20:43.675 --> 20:47.145
- I guess we'll just
have to try again next year.

20:47.212 --> 20:50.082
<i>[distant music]</i>

20:50.148 --> 20:51.750
- Do you guys hear that?

20:51.817 --> 20:54.152
- It sounds like sick beats.

20:54.219 --> 20:56.955
- [gasps] I'd know that
music from anywhere.

20:57.022 --> 20:58.957
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:59.024 --> 21:00.392
- What up, people?

21:00.459 --> 21:02.461
Who wants to do some
trick-or-treating?

21:02.527 --> 21:04.096
all: Technobear!
- You came!

21:04.162 --> 21:07.599
Yeah!
[all shouting joyfully]

21:08.700 --> 21:11.169
{\an1}- But Technobear,
what about the club?

21:11.236 --> 21:13.405
{\an3}- Yeah, well, I realized
I'm gonna have

21:13.472 --> 21:15.774
plenty of time to dance
with hotties in my life.

21:15.841 --> 21:19.711
{\an3}Right now, I just want to get
some candy with my buddies.

21:21.580 --> 21:24.249
All right, let's do this!

21:24.316 --> 21:27.452
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

21:27.519 --> 21:31.056
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:31.123 --> 21:32.624
<i>[doorbell ringing]</i>

21:32.691 --> 21:39.631
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:52.177 --> 21:54.446
- Happy Halloween to all,

21:54.513 --> 21:57.115
and to all a good fright!

21:57.182 --> 21:59.718
Whoo!
[laughing]

22:01.420 --> 22:04.556
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

22:04.623 --> 22:11.563
<i>♪ ♪</i>
